      "note_no": "23",
      "note": "The term khulata' (sing, khalit) denotes, literally, \"people who mix [i.e., are familiar or intimate] with others\" or \"with one another\". In the present instance it evidently alludes to the \"brotherhood\" between the two mysterious litigants, and is therefore best rendered as \"kinsmen\"."
